                  </persName>
             spoke to me, and we went into the house again; we went to the bar, we had a quartern of gin, and made three outs of it. The prisoner took out a key from his breeches pocket, he held the key up in his right hand; it was a skeleton key. From the description that I had of the prisoner, and his holding the key up, I concluded that he was the man that was going to commit the robbery. The prisoner and 
               <persName id="t18140914-69-person698">
                  Joe 
                  Golding
